    "body": "I use only zoxide as part of my own overengineered bashrc and I'm seeing the same problem. \r\n\r\nI use `jobs -l` in my function for PROMPT_COMMAND and every time I change directory I see:\r\n```\r\n[1]  3955696 Done                    \\command zoxide add -- \"${__zoxide_oldpwd}\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nI just took the \"quick & dirty\" solution of grepping it out with `jobs -l | grep -v zoxide` but IMHO there is something going on with zoxide and bg jobs. ",
