    "body": "> I'm not sure why changing the order of initialization fixes it\r\n\r\nCould it just be that perhaps executing zoxide first gives enough time for the hook to be done and not being detected by starship?\r\n\r\nI experimented putting a `sleep 1` just before my `jobs -l` and I see:\r\n```\r\n[1]  3492748 Done                    sleep 1\r\n```\r\nNo sign of zoxide task anymore. This happens even without zoxide installed. \r\n\r\nSorry for my ignorance, but perhaps there is a special behavior from bash side in relation with PROMPT_COMMAND? Are you hooking your function with this bash feature?",
