    "updated_at": "2023-06-14T22:43:45Z",
    "body": "Awesome! The patch has not made it into the latest point release of bash yet (currently 5.2.9) so I suspect it'll be quite some time before it's generally available to most bash users. Given that, I think it would be best if we patched this (we were making efforts to support users on Scientific Linux 6 up until last year, and that thing was shipping software from 2009).\r\n\r\nThe delta you suggested with calling jobs and redirecting to devnull works for me. Would you mind submitting a PR with that line and a comment explaining why it's necessary, and I'll approve it?",
